3.30	Integrated_Security_Unit	Integrated Security Unit	Integrated Security Unit (ISU) (French: ) is a joint-services infrastructure security unit created to secure major events in Canada. This administrative and operational entity was first created by the Royal Canadian Mounted Police (RCMP) in 2003.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Security_guard_training_at_a_portal_at_the_Whistler_Olympic_and_Paralympic_Village.jpg/250px-Security_guard_training_at_a_portal_at_the_Whistler_Olympic_and_Paralympic_Village.jpg
